15
00:01:09,304 --> 00:01:14,865
So let's start to give a look at 
the properties of the left-handed

16
00:01:14,865 --> 00:01:16,793
and right-handed waves.

17
00:01:17,013 --> 00:01:22,354
We will do that by first recalling 
the dispersion relation

18
00:01:22,354 --> 00:01:26,075
and then by looking at what is 
the range of frequency

19
00:01:26,145 --> 00:01:30,699
and wavenumber in which 
these waves can propagate.

20
00:01:32,032 --> 00:01:36,151
The dispersion relation for 
the right-handed waves reads as

21
00:01:37,274 --> 00:02:00,377
the index of refraction equal to
K²c²/ω² = (ω-ωR)(ω+ωL)/((ω-|Ωe|)(ω+Ωi))

22
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:04,866
