23
00:02:05,539 --> 00:02:09,393
The left-handed waves, on the other hand 
are such that

24
00:02:09,515 --> 00:02:39,254
K²c²/ω² = (ω+ωR)(ω-ωL)/((ω+|Ωe|)(ω-Ωi))

25
00:02:39,518 --> 00:02:42,097
These are the left-handed waves.

26
00:02:42,321 --> 00:02:45,402
Just let's recall for a second

27
00:02:45,973 --> 00:02:49,802
why these waves are called this way.

28
00:02:51,611 --> 00:02:55,457
So why are these waves called 
right- and left-handed waves?

29
00:02:55,646 --> 00:02:59,763
Let's draw our coordinates system.

30
00:03:01,703 --> 00:03:04,487
x,y,z,

31
