00:03:24,038 --> 00:03:29,546
that this electric field rotates 
according to the right hand rule

35
00:03:29,546 --> 00:03:34,849
with respect to B₀ if we are dealing 
with the right-handed waves

36
00:03:35,556 --> 00:03:40,816
while it moves in opposite direction 
for the left-handed waves.

37
00:03:41,509 --> 00:03:46,461
The frequencies that I have 
introduced here, ωR and ωL

38
00:03:46,561 --> 00:03:49,703
are defined such that

39
00:03:49,703 --> 00:04:06,174
ωR = 1/2 { |Ωe| + sqrt( Ωe² + 4 ωpe² ) }

40
00:04:06,205 --> 00:04:07,753
and let me point out that

41
00:04:07,753 --> 00:04:14,916
this is a quantity that is larger 
than the electron cyclotron frequency,

42
00:04:15,317 --> 00:04:22,607
while 
ωL = 1/2 {-|Ωe| + sqrt( Ωe² + 4 ωpe² ) }

43
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:25,757
that is a quantity that is 
larger than zero.

44
00:04:26,392 --> 00:04:28,774
What are the properties of these waves?

45
00:04:31,093 --> 00:04:34,426
First of all, in order to propagate,

46
00:04:35,337 --> 00:04:42,893
these waves should have a frequency 
such that this quantity here

47
00:04:43,153 --> 00:04:47,006
or this quantity here is positive.

48
00:04:47,006 --> 00:04:50,571
As K² c² / ω² is positive

49
00:04:51,256 --> 00:04:54,077
and if ω

50
00:04:54,411 --> 00:05:00,082
is found to be in between 
the electron cyclotron frequency |Ωe|

51
00:05:00,246 --> 00:05:06,799
and ωR ... I remind you that 
this inequality is valid

52
00:05:06,799 --> 00:05:13,897
then this quantity here, - as 
these other two terms are always positive,

