00:07:06,546 --> 00:07:08,278
will tend to 1.

74
00:07:08,702 --> 00:07:15,546
In other words, we will have 
that ω/K will be equal to c.

75
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:18,064
What will happen?

76
00:07:18,064 --> 00:07:25,104
Basically we will have waves that 
are propagating at the speed of light.

77
00:07:25,596 --> 00:07:30,246
There are electromagnetic waves, 
the plasma has no time

78
00:07:30,296 --> 00:07:35,280
to respond at frequencies 
that are so high.

79
00:07:36,748 --> 00:07:44,522
There will be therefore 
an asypmtote here that is ω/K = c

80
00:07:45,748 --> 00:07:48,981
where these waves will tend to.

81
00:07:49,434 --> 00:07:54,577
And then how about 
the limit of ω going to zero

82
00:07:55,134 --> 00:07:57,700
and K going to zero?

83
00:07:57,796 --> 00:08:03,369
We will have that 
K² c² / ω²

84
00:08:04,095 --> 00:08:10,457
will be equal to... -- we will be able 
to neglect ω with respect to ωR,

85
00:08:10,837 --> 00:08:13,319
ωL, |Ωe|, and Ωi.

86
00:08:13,319 --> 00:08:22,252
... therefore, this will be equal to
