00:08:29,624 --> 00:08:33,978
Now if we explicit the product of 
ωR and ωL,

90
00:08:33,978 --> 00:08:46,417
we find 
ωpe² / (|Ωe| Ωi)

91
00:08:46,485 --> 00:08:51,776
Now we can explicitly write that 
the expression for the plasma frequency

92
00:08:51,776 --> 00:08:58,724
that is 
ωpe² = e² n₀ / ( ε₀ me )

93
00:08:59,257 --> 00:09:15,004
and then we can write explicitly the
1/ (|Ωe| Ωi ) term as mi me / (e² B₀²)

94
00:09:15,066 --> 00:09:16,781
We can simplify e² .

95
00:09:16,781 --> 00:09:19,356
We can simplify me and me

96
00:09:19,676 --> 00:09:31,232
and we get
mi n₀ / ( ε₀ B₀² ),

97
00:09:31,709 --> 00:09:42,926
which is equal --if we notice that 
ε₀ μ₀ = 1/c²,

98
00:09:43,046 --> 00:09:53,409
...to 
c² μ₀ mi n₀ / B₀²

99
00:09:54,895 --> 00:09:57,095
The quantity that

100
00:09:58,369 --> 00:10:05,384
I have just drawn here is actually 
the inverse of a square speed, 1/cA².

101
00:10:05,881 --> 00:10:10,717
The speed cA that is called 
<i>Alfvén speed</i>.

102
00:10:11,650 --> 00:10:17,066
If we look at this we notice 
that c² and c² simplify

103
00:10:17,066 --> 00:10:20,611
and therefore that

104
00:10:21,420 --> 00:10:25,746
ω² = cA² K² .

105
00:10:26,076 --> 00:10:31,357
This implies that there is 
another asymptote

106
00:10:31,898 --> 00:10:37,617
that is given by ω/K = cA.

107
00:10:39,724 --> 00:10:45,788
We have now all the elements to derive 
the relationship between ω and K

108
00:10:45,788 --> 00:10:48,678
for the right-handed waves 
and the left-handed waves.

109
00:10:49,348 --> 00:10:52,245
Let's start by considering 
the right-handed waves.

110
00:10:52,490 --> 00:10:55,167
First of all, what we see is that

111
00:10:55,337 --> 00:10:59,248
for ω going to zero, K tends to zero,

