153
00:14:17,678 --> 00:14:22,201
and that the relationship between ω and K

154
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:24,221
is given by something like that.

155
00:14:24,605 --> 00:14:27,560
In this range of frequency 
that we are considering here,

156
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:30,279
we are looking at frequencies 
that are much larger than

157
00:14:30,437 --> 00:14:36,127
the ion cyclotron frequency
but much smaller than the electron one.

158
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:40,892
We are looking at waves that are 
propagating in this region here.

159
00:14:42,063 --> 00:14:48,052
What does the dispersion relation look 
like in this range of frequencies ?

160
00:14:48,052 --> 00:15:08,519
We have 
K²c²/ω² = (ω-ωR)(ω+ωL)/((ω-|Ωe|)(ω+Ωi))

161
00:15:08,712 --> 00:15:14,530
We can leave the denominator 
of this expression as it is,

162
00:15:14,883 --> 00:15:18,543
and for the numerator 
we can develop this product

163
00:15:18,575 --> 00:15:29,693
and we have 
ω² + ω(ωL-ωR) - ωL ωR

164
00:15:29,793 --> 00:15:35,486
Now this, in the regime of interest 
can be actually simplified

165
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:38,527
-up to now we haven't done 
any simplification,

166
00:15:38,527 --> 00:15:44,754
and in particular ω can be neglected 
with respect to |Ωe|

167
00:15:45,077 --> 00:15:50,514
and Ωi can be neglected with respect to ω.

168
00:15:50,798 --> 00:15:56,773
We've also that ωL is typically 
smaller than ωR

169
00:15:56,773 --> 00:15:58,933
and therefore it can be neglected
in the term ( ωL- ωR),

170
00:15:59,053 --> 00:16:13,484
and therefore this can be written as
{-ω(ω-ωR) + ωL ωR}/(|Ωe| ω)

171
00:16:13,733 --> 00:16:17,414
Now ω and ω here can be simplified,

172
00:16:17,414 --> 00:16:21,129
ω can be neglected with respect to ωR

173
00:16:21,129 --> 00:16:26,137
and in the limit of ωpe 
smaller than |Ωe|,

174
00:16:26,137 --> 00:16:29,582
ωR becomes comparable to |Ωe|.

175
00:16:29,582 --> 00:16:32,119
What we have therefore here is 1

176
00:16:33,262 --> 00:16:36,679
and then the product of ωL and ωR

177
00:16:36,679 --> 00:16:41,429
gives the plasma frequency squared ωpe²,

178
00:16:41,685 --> 00:16:45,764
that is then divided by ω |Ωe|.

179
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:52,461
Now this, as we've already said 
is larger than |Ωe| and ω

