00:17:21,772 --> 00:17:26,255
Now these terms are constant: c, ωpe, |Ωe|

185
00:17:26,696 --> 00:17:29,477
and therefore ω/K

186
00:17:29,972 --> 00:17:34,240
is proportional essentially 
to square root of ω

187
00:17:34,476 --> 00:17:38,380
which implies that the square root of ω

188
00:17:39,001 --> 00:17:41,080
is proportional to K

189
00:17:41,591 --> 00:17:44,555
which implies that
-if we want to evaluate

190
00:17:45,895 --> 00:17:51,221
the group of velocity of the wave 
by deriving ω with respect to K,

